    AbstractType
    Instances of the class AbstractType represent a type value assignable to a YamlElement's value, each separate type has its own methods and implementation, however they can all be cast to GenericType as it has the parameter <T> set to Object, therefore each subtype of this class can be cast to it.

    GenericType
    Instances of the class GenericType carry a value of type Object, essentially acting as an Any type, as the same suggests, this class' sole purpose is to allow interchangeability between types and generification of types.
